topic.title: Ingress DPU Completion (IngressDpuCpl)

body.p: Ingress DPU Completion message supports different message lengths depending on total number of input blocks.

table.title: Supported Ingress DPU Completion Message Length

* Message Length field in message header is Local Message Length plus one if it is for cascading, otherwise Message Length field is same as Local Message Length.

description.p: This field encodes error status associated with a message handle.
In an outbound message queue this field encodes corresponding message processing status.
In an inbound message queue, a value other than zero in this field indicates that the message handle should not be processed (i.e., it is an error or should be nullified).

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: PI1 detects PI field checking error.
PI2 detects PI field checking error.

description.p: This bit reports PI1 engine data integrity error if it is set to 1. The PI engine integrity error is data integrity check error detected alone data path and control path inside PI engine. When it is set to 0, no PI engine error is detected. When this bit is set, MsgStatus should be set to 3 (DiError).

This bit reports misalignment of the end of PI1 engine input data stream with PI1 block boundary if it is set to 1. In that case, the remaining data is forwarded by PI1 engine to PI1 output data stream. If it is set to 0, the P1 engine input data stream is aligned to PI1 block size.

This bit reports PI2 engine integrity error if it is set to 1. The PI1 engine integrity error is data integrity check error detected alone data path and control path inside PI2 engine. When it is set to 0, no PI2 engine error is detected. When this bit is set, MsgStatus should be set to 3 (DiError)

This bit reports misalignment the end of PI2 engine input data stream to PI2 block boundary if it is set to 1. In that case, the remaining data is forwarded by PI2 engine to PI2 output data stream. If it is set to 0, the P2 engine input data stream is aligned to PI2 block size.
This field contains the first PI check error status of PI1 or PI2.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: Guard and Application Tag fields mismatch.
Guard and Reference Tag fields mismatch.
Application Tag and Reference Tag fields mismatch

description.p: When this field is set other than 0, MsgStatus should set to 8 (PI1Err) or 9 (PI2Err) depending on the 1st PI error is detected in PI1 or PI2.

This bit reports Hash engine data integrity error if it is set to 1. The Hash engine data integrity error is data integrity check error detected alone data path and control path inside Hash engine. When it is set to 0, no Hash engine error is detected.
When this bit set to 1, MsgStatus is set to 3 (DiError)

This bit reports misalignment the end of hash engine input data stream to hash block boundary if it is set to 1. In that case, the remaining data is not hashed. If it is set to 0, the hash engine input data stream is aligned to hash block size.

This bit reports compression engine data integrity error if it is set to 1. The compression engine data integrity error is data integrity check error detected alone data path and control path inside compression engine. When it is set to 0, no compression engine error is detected.
When this bit is set to 1, MsgStatus should be set to 3 (DiError)

This bit reports misalignment the end of compression engine input data stream to uncompressed block boundary if it is set to 1. In that case, the remaining data is forwarded by compression engine to compression output data stream. If it is set to 0, the compression engine input data stream is aligned to uncompressed block size.

This bit reports encryption engine data integrity error if it is set to 1. The encryption engine internal error is data integrity check error detected alone data path and control path inside encryption engine. When it is set to 0, no encryption engine error is detected.
When this bit is set to 1, MsgStatus should be set to 3 (DiError)

This bit reports misalignment of the end of encryption engine input data stream to encryption block boundary if it is set to 1. In that case, the remaining data is forwarded by encryption engine to encryption output data stream. If it is set to 0, the encryption engine input data stream is aligned to encryption block size.
This bit reports mismatch data encryption key tag if it is set to 1. If it set to 0, the data encryption key tag is checked successfully.
When this bit is set, MsgStatus is set to 10 (EncrDEKTagMis)
This bit reports destination SGL overflow when output data stream length is larger than total memory size specified by destination SGL.
If it is set to 0, no destination SGL overflow is detected. If it is set to 1, destination SGL overflow is detected, and output data stream beyond the total memory size specified SGL is discarded.
When this bit is set to 1, MsgStatus is set to 11 (DstSGLOverflow)
The bit indicates the the completion type.

description.desc-title: Meta Data for Block 0- Compressed Data Block Count
description.p: This field contains the compressed data block counter in byte for input uncompressed data block 0 in block based compression mode.

description.desc-title: Meta Data for Block 0- Compressed Data Block Type
description.p: This field contains the compressed data block type for input uncompressed data block 0 in block based compression mode.

field-enum-def.field-enum-desc: Compressed data block contains compressed data with static Huffman encoding
Compressed data block contains original uncompressed data

description.desc-title: Meta Data for Block 0 - Compressed Data Length
description.p: This field contains the compressed data length in byte for the input uncompressed data block 0 in block based compression mode.

description.desc-title: Hash Digest 0 or Compression Meta Data 1-8
description.p: If there is one and only one SHA3-256 digest generated, and HashDigest0Offset=0, this field contains the SHA3-256 digest.

Otherwise, this field contains meta data for input uncompressed data block 8:1 in block based compression mode. The compression meta data CompMD[x] consists of CompMD[x].BlkCnt, CompMD[x].BlkTyp, and CompMD.Length as defined for CompMD[0] above. If the input uncompressed data block x (1<=x<=8) does not exist, CompMD[x] is ignored.

description.desc-title: Hash Digest 0 or Compression Meta Data 9-16
description.p: If hash operation is enabled for SHA3-256 and HashDigest0Offset=1, this field contains the SHA3-256 digest 0.
If hash operation is enabled for SHA3-512 this field contains the lower 256 byte SHA3-512 digest 0.

If hash operation is disabled, this field contains compression meta data 9-16. The compression meta data CompMD[x] consists of CompMD[x].BlkCnt, CompMD[x].BlkTyp, and CompMD.Length as defined for CompMD[0] above. If the input uncompressed data block x (9<=x<=16) does not exist, CompMD[x] is ignored.

description.desc-title: Hash Digest 1 or Compression Meta Data 17-24
description.p: If hash operation is enabled for SHA3-256, this field contains the SHA3-256 digest 1 if it exists.
If hash operation is enabled for SHA3-512 this field contains the high 256 byte SHA3-512 digest 0.

If hash operation is disabled, this field contains compression meta data 17-24. The compression meta data CompMD[x] consists of CompMD[x].BlkCnt, CompMD[x].BlkTyp, and CompMD.Length as defined for CompMD[0] above. If the input uncompressed data block x (17<=x<=24) does not exist, CompMD[x] is ignored.

description.desc-title: Hash Digest 2 or Compression Meta Data 25-32
description.p: If hash operation is enabled for SHA3-256 and this field contains the SHA3-256 digest 2.
If hash operation is enabled for SHA3-512 this field contains the lower 256 byte SHA3-512 digest 1.

If hash operation is disabled, this field contains compression meta data 25-32. The compression meta data CompMD[x] consists of CompMD[x].BlkCnt, CompMD[x].BlkTyp, and CompMD.Length as defined for CompMD[0] above. If the input uncompressed data block x (25<=x<=32) does not exist, CompMD[x] is ignored.
